hm.binkley.util.logging.osi

Enum SupportLoggers

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SupportLoggers>
      • hm.binkley.util.logging.osi.SupportLoggers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SupportLoggers>

    public enum SupportLoggers
extends Enum<SupportLoggers>
    SupportLoggers are custom MarkedLoggers for specialized use. Methods create new marked loggers with the enum names as markers.

    There is one factory method variant for each style of logger creation:

    getLogger(Class)
    Creates a new underlying logger from a class
    getLogger(String)
    Creates a new underlying logger from a logger name
    getLogger(Logger)
    Reuses an existing underlying logger

    Applications should configure logback or other logging system by marker:

    ALERT
    Send alerts for system issues
    APPLICATION
    Logs normally following logback configuration
    AUDIT
    Records an audit trail, typically to a database
    TRACE
    A tracing logger for method entry and exit
    Author:
    B. K. Oxley (binkley)

        public static final SupportLoggers ALERT
